      "date": "2014-10-06 16:16:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI would like to know why Intel changes the authority of the original patches porting them to other branches. in most of the cases I do not see serious rewrites in commits so that that change would be reasonable. is it possible to learn --author option at the end ? is it possible to renew patches which are not landed yet ?",
